Peru Stocks: Alturas, Casa Grande, Intergroup, Southern, Volcan

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-07-08T18:34:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-08/peru-stocks-alturas-casa-grande-intergroup-southern-volcan.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 2:21 p.m.  New York  time.  The  Lima  General Index fell 0.2 percent to 19,822.43. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index gained 1.1 percent to 2,549.72.  Industrial, mining and banking stocks slumped as U.S.
shares dropped on lower-than-forecast jobs growth, said Gustavo Urrutia, the chief economist at brokerage Inteligo SAB in Lima.  Alturas Minerals Corp. (ALT)  , a Canadian copper and gold
exploration company, fell 6.7 percent to 14 cents after copper
declined in New York.  Casa Grande  (CASAGRC1 PE), Peru’s largest
sugar producer and a unit of Gloria SA, dropped 2 percent to 15
soles as futures fell in New York. Volcan Cia Minera SAA
(VOLCABC1 PE), Peru’s largest zinc producer, slid 1.4 percent to
2.90 soles.  Intergroup Financial Services Corp. (IFS)  , owner
of Peru’s fourth-largest bank, slid 0.8 percent to $25.10.  Southern Copper Corp. (SCCO)  , Peru’s biggest copper
producer, rose for the fourth day in five, adding 4.2 percent to
$34.40 as investors bet the company will produce a new
environmental impact study for its Tia Maria copper deposit,
Urrutia said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
